Barney lives and skis in Vermont now and his favorite ski resort is wherever he is skiing at the time\!

I believe you should “carve diem.” You know, like the Latin carpe diem which means seize the day. In skiing a carve turn is the best kind of turn you can do. Thus carve diem means carve the day. Clever huh? Also, I ski, therefore I am. Finally, to ski or not to ski, that is not a question\!
